{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fdc36993-6d56-4226-9bb6-55f89a0e434e","content":"The project needs to be configured for Microsoft.Testing.Platform. I'll update the csproj to enable the MTP runner and add the HangDump extension.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01G8vYCGXAhCNucpVtoCyHog","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-1ae59f06c5a34e8d9fe304e576b72b17/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" Version=\"1.6.2\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-1ae59f06c5a34e8d9fe304e576b72b17/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"397ab46a-54d7-4fbb-b291-12a2ebaafa14","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The error says the project is using VSTest runner, not Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The global.json says to use Microsoft.Testing.Platform, but the project isn't configured for it. I need to add `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` to the project file, or use `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>`.\n\nActually, with MSTest 3.8.0 and .NET 10, the project needs `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` or `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in the csproj.\n\n\nLet me look into the MSTest documentation more carefully. With MSTest 3.3 and later, I can either set `<UseVSTest>false</UseVSTest>` or `<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>` to switch away from VSTest. Since the global.json is already configured for Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I just need to enable the right property in the project file to match that configuration. `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` should be enough, though `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` might get set automatically in newer versions. With MSTest 3.8.0, I should also consider adding the hangdump extension package for better diagnostics, though I need to verify whether it's bundled or needs separate installation with this version.","outputTokens":1223,"requestId":"67D8:325178:164E85D:1918A63:69FD3A29"},"id":"e9d672c8-83c2-46eb-a558-4e018b382e1c","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:19:58.476Z","parentId":"460adaa5-ca56-4184-9df1-4171cf7eee76"}
